    <item>
      <title>Blackjack Overview</title>
      <link>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/engineering/domains/games/domains/gambling/domains/blackjack/texts/blackjack-overview/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 09 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/engineering/domains/games/domains/gambling/domains/blackjack/texts/blackjack-overview/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Audience: readers familiar with basic &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/engineering/domains/games/domains/card-games/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;card game&lt;/a&gt; vocabulary and &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/engineering/domains/games/domains/gambling/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;gambling&lt;/a&gt; fundamentals.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Learning goal: explain blackjack&amp;rsquo;s turn structure, the player&amp;rsquo;s main decision points, and the rule changes that most affect expected value.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;worked-example-hard-16-against-a-dealer-10&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#worked-example-hard-16-against-a-dealer-10&#34; class=&#34;heading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Link to this section&#34;&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;Worked example: hard 16 against a dealer 10&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Suppose your first two cards are 10 and 6. The dealer&amp;rsquo;s &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/engineering/domains/games/domains/gambling/domains/blackjack/terms/upcard/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;upcard&lt;/a&gt; is a 10. You therefore hold a &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/engineering/domains/games/domains/gambling/domains/blackjack/terms/hard-hand/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;hard hand&lt;/a&gt; totaling 16 against one of the dealer&amp;rsquo;s strongest visible starting positions.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
